Facebook stigmatism:  Liking your own post makes you a narcissist and is unnecessary.  Truth:  I want to break their ranking algorithm to pieces.

Brian
Not that I don't want to be a bot, I think you are hilarious dude.

Just wanted you to know why so you don't think poorly of me
Well thank you, and I've never judged a self-liker regardless. Good luck in your endeavor!

Brian
I appreciate your insights.
Are you Christian?
That's a complicated question.

Brian
I have a complicated answer.
You have an answer to the question of whether or not I am a Christian?
Brian

Brian
I have an answer to your question you haven't asked yet.
And if you can't answer that question, I can help give you clarity, because I have already had every argument on the topic of Christianity.

Oh, do tell.
The problem for me is that it depends on how you define "Christian".

Brian
Someone that believes Christ as a genius and figured out how to prioritize his love and things that matter to him like being a good person or what we interpret as the ideal perfect person.
Yeah okay then. Not everyone would agree with that description. Most notably Keifer.

Brian
I bet he would if he knew as much as you.
What do you disagree with?
Oh no, I don't disagree at all, but I don't have a set definition for the word "Christian" but it often has some pretty negative connotations in my experience.

Brian
What is your definition?

**Just FYI, I'm going to be really annoyed and/or impressed if this turns out to be a bot.
I guess I would say someone who worships Jesus as god.
And I suppose the exclusivity of that belief also. That Jesus is God and others are not.
I wouldn't necessarily agree with that.

Brian
My wife tells me God exists in all of us, and I finally believe it to the fullest.
Exactly! That I like. Taking the Bible literally on the other hand, no es bueno.

Brian
Matthew 5:44 (KJV)  But I say unto you, Love your enemies, bless 
them that curse you, do good to them that hate you, and pray for them 
which despitefully use you, and persecute you;
Pertinent to you?
Yes, there are many "diamonds in the dunghill". The parts about killing gays and such I'm not so keen on tho.

Brian

I was going to say, How does God justify lying to us?
God saves the world by lying to us?

Brian
Yes.  Imagine everything Jesus does is a magic trick (I am sure that won't be hard for you).  What is the difference between magic and miracles?  What is more important that the words on a page is the reason for it, Jesus ambition was to teach us to be good people.  That is how he saves the world.

Brian
*more important than
Interesting theory..

Brian
If you learn to believe it you can create "coincidences" for others and use the world to make miracles.  I am already planning.
Not sure I follow.

Brian
I am sending a gift to a person from another person other than myself.  What kind of connection would that create?
Not much of a connection as far as you're concerned.

Brian
Exactly, that is what it means to truly live for others.
Okay.

Brian
